\{a,b,k,l\}
(ax+by)dx+(kx+ly)dy=0
I(x,y)dx+J(x,y)dy=0
F
\frac{\partial F(x,y)}{\partial x}=I
\frac{\partial F(x,y)}{\partial y}=J
I=ax+by
J=kx+ly
F
\frac{\partial F(x,y)}{\partial x}=ax+by
\frac{\partial F(x,y)}{\partial y}=kx+ly
F
\frac{\partial F}{\partial x}=ax+by
h(y)
F=\frac{1}{2}ax^2+bxy+h(y)
\frac{\partial F}{\partial y}=kx+ly
F=bx+h'(y)=kx+ly
h'(y)=kx+ly-bx
\Rightarrow h=kxy+\frac{1}{2}ly^2-bxy
F=\frac{1}{2}ax^2+kxy+\frac{1}{2}ly^2
\frac{\partial F}{\partial x} \neq ax+by
 (ax+by)dx+(kx+ly)dy =0 \implies  M=ax+by,\quad N=kx+ly 
\implies  M_y=b,\quad N_x=k .
 M_y=N_x. 
